TS = Telesync = The syncing of one video source with a separate audio source. More often than not, a CAM is the video source, but not always. Could be a foreign language video source (Cam or other), synced with another language audio source (Cam or Line).

Anyhow, fetched from wikipedia: "A telesync (TS)[1] is a bootleg recording of a film recorded in a movie theater, often (although not always) filmed using a professional camera on a tripod in the projection booth, the audio of a TS is captured with a direct connection to the sound source (often an FM microbroadcast provided for the hearing-impaired, or from a drive-in theater)."
